# shadcn UI

This project uses **shadcn UI** for all UI elements. Prefer shadcn components over custom or other UI libraries.

## Initialization

If shadcn is not yet initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding components

To add a specific component, use the add command. Example for the button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the component name you need (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `dropdown-menu`). Check [shadcn UI components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for the full list.

## Guidelines

- Use only shadcn UI components for buttons, forms, dialogs, cards, and other UI elements.
- If a component is missing, install it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>` before implementing the feature.
- Keep in mind the project's theming, that means no dark text on dark backgrounds and no light text on light backgrounds
